The paper deals with routing on geometric graphs, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of constraints and obstacles in the routing problem suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of competitive routing strategies suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of game theory (cs.GT) and robotics (cs.RO).
